Police have said they are following a "positive line of inquiry" following the death of a man in Bishopbriggs. Murder inquiry launched by police after Bishopbriggs death Police have said they are following a &quot;positive line of inquiry&quot; following the death of a man in Bishopbriggs.
John McFarlane, 28, was seriously injured near his home in Auchinairn Road at about 22:35 on Thursday. 
He died a short time later at Glasgow Royal Infirmary.
Officers are investigating a disturbance on Springfield Road, close to Auchinairn Road, in which Mr McFarlane is thought to have been attacked.
A report will be submitted to the procurator fiscal.
 